### Step 4: Switch Back to Main and Make a Conflicting Change

Go back to the main branch:

```bash
git checkout main
```

Now modify the same file differently:

```bash
echo "Main branch change" > app.txt
```

Stage and commit:

```bash
git add app.txt
git commit -m "Conflicting update from main"
```

At this point:

* `feature-1` has one version of the file
* `main` has a different version

This sets up a merge conflict.

